The paper focuses on reinforcement learning for robots to solve complex, multi-step tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of reward shaping and visual tasks also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of a model to learn and improve performance, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the focus on task completion and failure consequences suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY).
